      "side": 1,
      "message": "Maybe! Internet searching suggests the 3-\u003e4 change was deprecating a feature and changing the return code of a function, which seem like things we could avoid. It doesn\u0027t seem necessary though since all our supported platforms do have some .so.4 and on debian, the .so.3s are just symlinks to the .so.4s anyway. I\u0027ve removed the .so.3s.",
